'''Emam Ashour Metwally Abdel Ghany''' ({{langx|ar|إمام عاشور متولي عبد الغني}}; born 20 February 1998) is an Egyptian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Egyptian Premier League]] club [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]].

==Club career==
===Ghazl El Mahlla===
Ashour began his career in the youth sector of [[Ghazl El Mahalla SC|Ghazl El Mahalla]] and progressed through all of the club's youth teams. He was promoted to the first team for El Mahalla and then moved to [[Haras El Hodoud SC|Haras El Hodoud]] on loan for a season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2018/7/22/صور-الحدود-يحصل-علي-خدمات-امام-عاشور-لاعب-المحلة/3882700 |title=صور.. الحدود يحصل علي خدمات "امام عاشور " لاعب المحلة |website=youm7.com |date=23 July 2019}}</ref>

===Haras El Hodoud===
====2018–19====
On 19 October 2018, Emam Ashour equalized for Haras El Hodoud by scoring the first goal against [[Smouha SC|Smouha]], in the match held between the two teams at [[Borg El Arab Stadium]], in the 11th round of the Premier League.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2018/10/19/فيديو-إمام-عاشور-يتعادل-لحرس-الحدود-أمام-سموحة-1-1/3996489 |title=فيديو.. إمام عاشور يتعادل لحرس الحدود أمام سموحة 1 / 1 |website=youm7.com |date=19 October 2018}}</ref>

On 26 November 2018, Emam Ashour scored the third goal for Haras El Hodood Club against its counterpart, [[Wadi Degla SC|Wadi Degla]], in the sixteenth round match of the league competition. Emam Ashour scored the goal in the 88th minute of the match against [[Mohamed Abdel Monsef]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2018/11/26/إمام-عاشور-يحرز-الهدف-الثالث-لحرس-الحدود-أمام-دجلة/4046234 |title=إمام عاشور يحرز الهدف الثالث لحرس الحدود أمام دجلة |website=youm7.com |date=26 November 2018}}</ref>

On 26 May 2019, Emam Ashour scored a goal against Wadi Degla, which the Guard equalized with a similar goal in the match that ended in a 1-1 draw.{{citation needed|date=July 2025}}

===Zamalek===
====2019–20====
On 4 August 2019, [[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]] officials signed contracts to include Emam Ashour, Ghazl El Mahalla playmaker, for 5 seasons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2019/8/4/صور-الزمالك-يضم-إمام-عاشور-من-المحلة-لمدة-5-مواسم/4362773 |title=صور.. الزمالك يضم إمام عاشور من المحلة لمدة 5 مواسم |website=youm7.com |date=4 August 2019}}</ref>

On 20 February 2020, the Disciplinary and Ethics Committee of the [[Egyptian Football Association]] decided, regarding the events of the Super Cup match that was held between the [[Al Ahly]] and Zamalek teams in the Emirati capital, [[Abu Dhabi]], to suspend Emam Ashour until the end of the season and fine each of them 100,000 pounds.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2020/2/23/تعرف-على-أول-رد-فعل-للاعب-إمام-عاشور-بعد-قرار/4642820 |title=تعرف على أول رد فعل للاعب إمام عاشور بعد قرار إيقافه لنهاية الموسم |website=youm7.com |date=23 February 2020}}</ref>

On 22 September 2020, Emam Ashour scored the third goal for Zamalek against [[Tanta SC|Tanta]] in the 96th minute of the match at [[Cairo International Stadium]] in the 29th round of the league, which ended with a score of 3/1 for Zamalek.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2020/9/22/إمام-عاشور-يحرز-الهدف-الثالث-للزمالك-في-مرمي-طنطا-بالوقت/4989225 |title=إمام عاشور يحرز الهدف الثالث للزمالك في مرمي طنطا بالوقت الضائع |website=youm7.com |date=22 September 2020}}</ref>

On 5 October 2020, Emam Ashour scored the equalizer in the 81st minute of the match in his team's match against [[Smouha SC|Smouha]] 2-1, in the round of 16 competitions in the [[Egyptian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2020/10/5/إمام-عاشور-بعد-فوز-الزمالك-أنا-صغير-ومتربى-ولست-بلطجى/5008185 |title=إمام عاشور بعد فوز الزمالك: أنا صغير ومتربى.. ولست "بلطجى" |website=youm7.com |date=5 October 2020}}</ref>

On 6 October 2020, the Disciplinary and Ethics Committee of the Football Association announced that Zamalek player Imam Ashour was suspended for one match and fined 50,000 pounds, for what he did in the match between Zamalek and [[Al Masry SC|Al Masry]], in the 31st round of the Egyptian League Championship, which ended with Zamalek's 1-0 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youm7.com/story/2020/10/6/لجنة-الانضباط-توصى-بتغريم-المصرى-50-ألف-جنيه-بسبب-الجماهير/5008793 |title=لجنة الانضباط توصى بتغريم المصرى 50 ألف جنيه بسبب الجماهير |website=youm7.com |date=6 October 2020}}</ref>

====2020–21====

On 9 January 2021, Emam Ashour scored two goals in his team's 3-0 win over [[Tala'ea El Gaish SC|Talaea El Gaish]] in the sixth round of the [[Egyptian Premier League]]. Emam Ashour was able to take the lead in the 49th minute with a missile shot. Ashour reappeared in the 71st minute to score the third goal for Zamalek after a shot into the far left corner of the Al-Talaea goalkeeper.

On 12 January 2021, Emam Ashour scored Zamalek's only goal with a shot in the 54th minute of the match, which Zamalek won 1-0 against [[Al Masry SC]]. Emam Ashour intercepted the ball the most and recovered it from Al-Masry for the benefit of Zamalek players, with a score of 20 times in the match, and he was the second player who received the ball the most from his teammates, with a score of 42 successful receptions, with a score of 100%, after [[Tarek Hamed]].

On 2 February 2021, Emam Ashour assisted a goal for [[Ferjani Sassi]] from a strike in the 69th minute of the match that Zamalek lost to [[Ghazl El Mahalla]] with a score of 2-1 at [[El Mahalla Stadium]] in the 11th round matches of the Egyptian Premier League.

On 7 February 2021, Emam assisted a goal for [[Youssef Obama]] in the 77th minute after a cross ball into the right side of the penalty area, and Obama headed it over, announcing his team's second goal in the match that Zamalek won 2-0 over [[Al-Ittihad Alexandria]] in the matches of the 12th round of the Egyptian league.

On 14 August 2021, Emam Ashour scored the first goal against Al-Ismaili with a powerful shot that collided with the [[Ismaily SC]] defender, changed direction, and entered the net in the 56th minute of the match, which ended with Zamalek's 2-0 win at [[Ismailia Stadium]] in the thirtieth round of the Egyptian Premier League competitions.

On 21 July 2022, Emam Ashour scored the second goal against [[Al Ahly]] with a perfect missile shot, in the match that was held on the grounds of [[Cairo International Stadium]], in the final of the [[2020–21 Egypt Cup|2021 Egypt Cup]].

===Midtjylland===
Ashour participated in 7 matches with [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in all competitions, which he scored two goals, one goal in the [[UEFA Europa League]], and another in the [[Danish Superliga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.elwatannews.com/ar/1/2/1043006/ماذا-قدم-إمام-عاشور-مع-ميتلاند-الدنماركي-قبل-انتقاله-إلى-الأهلي |title=ماذا قدم إمام عاشور مع ميتلاند الدنماركي قبل انتقاله إلى الأهلي؟ |website=elwatan sport |date=18 July 2023}}</ref>

===Al Ahly===
====2023–24====
On 18 July 2023, Ashour joined Al Ahly from [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] for 5 year contract,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2023/07/16/emam-ashour-al-ahly-move/ |title=Emam Ashour arrives at Al Ahly to complete summer move |website=KingFut |date=16 July 2023}}</ref> He was given the number 22 shirt, once worn by The legend [[Mohamed Aboutrika]].

On 15 September 2023, Ashour made his debut with [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] against  [[USM Alger]] in [[CAF Super Cup]].

On 15 December 2023, he scored his first goal in the FIFA Club World for Al Ahly in a 3–1 win over [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] in the [[2023 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]] second round.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/107/287833/287835/400017367 |title=Al Ahly FC 3–1 Al Ittihad FC |publisher=FIFA |date=15 December 2023 }}</ref>

During the first season, Emam Ashour contributed mainly to winning the [[CAF Champions League]] title for the twelfth time in Al-Ahly's history at the expense of [[ES Tunis]].
 
[[File:إمام عاشور وأول بطوله إفريقيه مع الأهلي.jpg|thumb|Emam Ashour celebrate his first [[CAF Champions League]] title with Al Ahly|220px]]

Emam Ashour also played an important role in achieving the [[Egypt Cup]] title at the expense of [[Zamalek SC]], after scoring a goal in the quarter-finals against [[ENPPI Club]] and then scoring the first goal in the tournament final against the White Knight.

He played an important role in Al-Ahly's journey in the Nile League, and succeeded in maintaining the championship title for the second season in a row. In general, Emam Ashour participated in the Al-Ahly club shirt in 40 matches in various tournaments, during which he scored 10 goals and assisted 9 other goals, thus contributing in 19 matches.

Therefore, Emam Ashour makes a scoring contribution, whether by scoring or assisting, with a goal rate in approximately every two matches, which is the highest rate among the team's current players who have completed a year. Regarding the Nile League Championship campaign,

After [[Wessam Abou Ali]], Ashour had the second most goal contributions among Al-Ahly players with 11, scoring seven and assisting four others.

====2024–25====
Ashour scored his first ever hat-trick on 11 January 2025 against [[Stade d'Abidjan]] in the group stage of the [[2024–25 CAF Champions League group stage|CAF Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ashour hat-trick powers Ahly|url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-champions-league/news/pyramids-clinch-historic-quarter-final-spot-ashour-hat-trick-powers-ahly/|publisher=CAF Online|date=11 January 2025 |access-date=11 January 2025 |language=en}}</ref>
 
[[File:Emam Ashour.jpg|thumb|Emam Ashour celebrate a goal title with Al Ahly in [[Egyptian Premier League]]|220px]]

In June 2025, Ashour was ruled out of Al Ahly’s squad for the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]] after suffering a broken collarbone during the opening match against [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Emam Ashour Ruled Out of Club World Cup |url=https://www.kingfut.com/2025/06/15/emam-ashour-ruled-out-of-club-world-cup/ |website=KingFut |date=15 June 2025 |access-date=31 July 2025
}}</ref>

== International career ==

He played for the [[Egypt national under-23 football team|Egypt U23]]  team in [[2023 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations|Egypt 2023]] when they got the first place and won the championship.

In 2021 he was called up by the [[Egypt national under-23 football team|Egyptian national Olympic team]] to participate in the Games of the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Olympics games]] in [[Tokyo]].

On 2 December 2025, Ashour was called up to the Egypt squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/egypt-name-final-28-man-squad-for-totalenergies-caf-afcon-2025-salah-leads-pharaohs-charge/|title=Egypt name final 28-man squad for TotalEnergies CAF AFCON 2025, Salah leads Pharaohs' charge|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=2 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

